    {
        "user": "U01B8031PM1",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1614178573.042500",
        "client_msg_id": "7b5086c6-163e-4506-b0e7-1021c28c7084",
        "text": "Driving up margin (to a limit) usually reduces adverse selection. All trading strategies, even well selected ones tend to exhibit out of sample overfit. If margin is high enough that usually means strategy ends up avoiding lots of trades which do nothing but cause noise PL and lastly alert the market to your impending trading direction.",
